5:
The Kweturs... killed the princess?
Wh-what are you talking about?
8:
N-nonsense! The head family would
never do such a thing!
11:
I hear the assassination was
disguised as a quest from
Palpebra's guild. Isn't that so, Velgar
Oinas?
15:
Velgar?! The guardsman that
betrayed the princess?! That Velgar
Oinas?!
22:
Now, speak. What will you do, o
servant of the Oxtans?
25:
Will your loyalty stay with House
Oxtan? Will it stay with the House
that controls it, the House that killed
Her Highness?
29:
Is this truly the path your Stars led
you down?! To cover for your
blood-soaked masters?!
39: Your Highness. I stand by your side.
48:
That is enough, Marden! I, Varen
Nialas, command you to stop!
57:
Such unlawful dealings will only
bring on division and enmity! I won't
allow it! He will be dealt with as the
law prescribes!
59:
If it is true that he did not know what
he was doing, his punishment will
reflect that fact. I will not stand for
any unnecessary threats!
63:
You cannot be serious, Your
Highness.
66:
The Oxtans are not the only ones
against the Swes' proposal. It is
House Kwetur who are holding the
reins.
68:
Therefore, it would be much wiser to
go ahead with my plan...
72:
I decided that I will listen to what
both House Oxtan and House Kwetur
have to say. Any punishment, if
necessary, will come after that.
76: Vyron... Are you fine with that?
80:
Sorry, kid. Stoppin' people like you
from going rogue is the one job I've
got left.
84:
Hahaha... I look like a fool... My whole
plan is in shambles...
89: Marden! What were you aiming for?!
92:
Armed with your alleged truth about
the assassination, you could have
confronted the Kweturs at any time.
Why take this long, winding road?
101: Your Highness, this is not the time...
105:
Don't worry, I know. Our priority right
now should be protecting the
people from the monsters.
108:
Let me investigate this place. I
promise that I will protect both you
and all the people of your lands.
111:
This facility was being used to
research monsters. There ought to
be some clue hidden in here.
118:
I will, for that is the path I have
chosen!
125:
I certainly wasn't expecting an
assassination from thirty years ago
to come to light right now.
130:
You knew about Velgar Oinas this
whole time and never said a word to
me? How cruel!
134:
I was tryin' to avoid a fuss like the
one we're having now.
138:
Our shock is the least of our issues.
Even if you're telling the truth, there
will be plenty of people who think
otherwise. This will split the kingdom
in half.
141:
And who knows what Palpebra will
do, considering they were accused
of being behind the assassination at
the time. This truth is a veritable
powder keg...
146:
Even then, I believe that with your
help, we will be able to stay on the
righteous path.
149:
If the Nine Houses stand together,
then we can make the truth public
and overcome any obstacles along
the way. Won't you lend House Swes'
aid?
154:
You shall have it. Your wish is also
ours.
162:
I don't mind. What I want to know is
how we plan on stoppin' the
monsters.
168:
Well... Putting the matter of the
assassination aside, we know that
the Star Augurs were involved with
the research facility.
172:
Tell me. Do you think that facility
may be what caused the monster
attack?
177:
I believe it's the opposite. They were
capturing monsters to study the
cause of their aggression.
180:
Of course, this is only conjecture, but
I believe that they wanted to take
credit for the research.
183:
They hid all proof of the Augurs'
involvement and quietly moved
researchers before forbidding
access to the facility.
185:
They probably wanted to use those
findings to solve our monster
problem, but only after removing all
traces of external help.
190:
But they couldn't do that if Palpebra
came and solved the issue before
they could take credit.
194:
Now that the truth has surfaced,
neither House will be able to oppose
Palpebra's involvement.
196:
In a way, things went according to
Marden's original plan. Now,
convincing the others to support
House Nouin will be much easier.
201:
So... we're back at having to
persuade House Tris?
205:
If we bring Palpebra into this,
Cieldeau will have no option but to
move as well.
211:
Failing to help House Nouin while a
foreign military rises to the occasion
would be very difficult to justify.
215:
In the end, this could make their
relationship with the Nouins even
worse. On the other hand, it never
was that good to begin with.
221:
In that regard... I actually have an
idea.
225:
There is a way to make all Houses
work alongside Palpebra without
any hostility.
229:
You intend to convince your brother
to accept House Tris' help?
232: I will. I must. Not only that...
236:
I believe it's time to rebuild the
Swallow Knights.
